        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 3 at 5:03PM CDT by NWS Springfield MO</headline>
        <description>At 502 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Hartville, or 15 miles west of Mountain Grove, moving northeast at 80
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Dawson, Competition, Mansfield, Manes, Huggins, Bucyrus, Hazelton,
Lynchburg, Graff, Falcon, Hartville, Success, Norwood, Roby, Plato,
Prescott, Houston, Bendavis, and Raymondville.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
